message.content:
cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on developing a deep neural network model for a humanoid robot to learn and integrate cognitive skills for perception, action, and decision making. The experiments conducted are synthetic robotic experiments, which further support the relevance of this paper to the Robotics sub-category. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The proposed model is built on a dynamic vision network, which processes and integrates direct perception of dynamic visuomotor patterns. This indicates the relevance of this paper to the Computer Vision sub-category. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a deep learning approach for developing adequate coordination among different cognitive processes of a humanoid robot. This indicates the relevance of this paper to the Artificial Intelligence sub-category. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep dynamic neural network model for end-to-end learning of direct perception of visuomotor stream. This indicates the relevance of this paper to the Machine Learning sub-category. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed model is a deep neural network model, which indicates the relevance of this paper to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing sub-category.
